label.value: lacks parts or has fewer parts of type

value.value: The bearer of this quality has_part < n of the indicated entity type, where n is the normal amount for a comparable organism. Note that the bearer of the quality is the whole, not the part. Formally: If a bearer entity e has fewer parts of type X at time t, then the number of instances x of X at t such that x part_of e is < n, where n is either the normal number for comparable entities, or n is stated explicitly. This case includes the limit case, where the bearer lacks all parts of the specified type.
A quality of physical entities inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking a physical part as specified by the additional entity.
The bearer of this quality has_part > n of the indicated entity type, where n is the normal amount for a comparable organism. Note that the bearer of the quality is the whole, not the part.
Surface shape that refers to the inward or outward curvature of the surface.
A shape that inheres in a 2 dimensional entity, such as a cross section or projection of a 3 dimensional entity.
A complete three dimensional shape in which for every line connecting pair of points on the object is within the object. Or: a shape lacking cavities. Contrast: concave.
A complete three dimensional shape in which there is a line connecting pair of points on the object that lies outside the object. Or: a shape with cavities. Contrast: concave.
A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the degree to which there are subdivisions or offshoots in a bearer entity.
A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer forms a bundle of anatomical fibers, as of muscle or nerve.
Having extra or fewer parts.

definition.value: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's processing the form of a thin plate sheet or layer.

value.value: A quality which inheres in a molecular entity, a single molecule, atom, ion, radical etc.
A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its constitution.
Texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being marked with one or more channels.
A shape that inheres in a 3 dimensional entity.
A quality that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.
A quality that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.
A quality of an object that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.
A quality of an object that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.
A shape constituting a transition between a rectangle and a circle; a closed curve, of which the circle and ellipse are special cases, whose parametric equation is x = a.cos2/rt, y = b.cos2/rt
An orientation inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's placement at an angle.
A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being located toward the base of an organism relative to another entity.
A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the presence of long chain aliphatic lipids on the surface of an organism.
A flavor quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having an acrid, sharp, or disagreeable flavor.

label.value: quality of interaction of a substance with electromagnetic radiation

value.value: A quality of a substance on which or through which electromagnetic radiation impinges or traverses with respect to radiation. This substance quality changes the quality of the incident radiation with respect to any of: intensity, direction, scatter and wavelength.

A plant experimental condition (PECO:0007359) or set of conditions describing the application of an abiotic (PECO:0007191) or biotic plant exposure (PECO:0007357) or the combinatorial application thereof.
A chemical exposure (PECO:0007189) involving the application of organic chemical(s).
A chemical exposure (PECO:0007189) involving the application of inorganic chemical(s).
An inorganic chemical exposure (PECO:0001004) involving the application of an anion or a mixture of anions (CHEBI:22563).
An organic chemical exposure (PECO:0001003) involving the application of a gas or mixture of gases.
A chemical exposure (PECO:0007189) that induces stress.
A chemical stress exposure (PECO:0001036) involving use of osmotic stress-inducing chemicals.
A chemical exposure (PECO:0007189) involving the use of antibiotic for selection purposes.

definition.value: An exposure to a chemical that has the role of antimicrobial agent

value.value: An exposure involving growth in the presence of non-mineral nutrients to study various types of responses.
A plant macronutrient exposure (PECO:0007240)  involving the use of the primary plant macronutrients nitrogen (N), phosphorus (P), and potassium (K).
An exposure involving the use of macronutrients (Ca, Mg, S) as supplement to study various types of responses. These macronutrients are used less often as fertilizers than the primary elements.
An exposure involving the exposure of plant to elemental forms of nutrients as supplement. These are not considered essential elements.
An exposure involving growing plants in soil growth media with varying contents.
An exposure involving the growth of a plant with the pathogen Cochliobolus spp.
An exposure involving growing plants in soil growth media of varying pH levels.
An exposure involving growing plants in acidic (low pH) soil growth media.
An exposure involving growing plants in basic (high pH) soil growth media.
A plant exposure (PECO:0001001) involving exposure to the various factors that comprise a geographical/regional location.
A growth hormone exposure (PECO:0007165) involving the use of cytokinin (or its homolog) growth hormone.

definition.value: An exposure to a chemical that has the role of cytokinin

value.value: A growth hormone exposure (PECO:0007165) involving the use of ethylene (or its homolog) growth hormone.
A growth hormone exposure (PECO:0007165) involving the use of auxin (or its homolog).

definition.value: An exposure to a chemical that has the role of auxin

value.value: A growth hormone exposure (PECO:0007165) involving the use of JA (or its homolog).
A plant nutrient exposure (PECO:0007241) involving the use of a fertilizer, a combination of plant nutrients.

definition.value: An exposure to a chemical that has the role of fertilizer
